https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FNYCPlanning%2Fstatus%2F1864789484874707198%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecame%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20latest%20local%20government%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-poised-legalize-tiny-backyard-homes-accessory-dwelling-units-housing-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejoin%20a%20nationwide%20push%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20more%20backyard%20tiny%20homes%20and%20converted%20basements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20US%20grapples%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.freddiemac.com%2Fresearch%2Fforecast%2F20241126-us-economy-remains-resilient-with-strong-q3-growth%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehousing%20shortage%3C%2Fa%3E%20that's%20sent%20home%20prices%20and%20rents%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fhome-prices-drop%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esoaring%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20cities%20and%20states%20are%20turning%20to%20accessory%20dwelling%20units%20to%20help%20solve%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20secondary%20units%20on%20lots%20with%20primary%20homes%20%E2%80%94%20largely%20in%20the%20form%20of%C2%A0backyard%20cottages%2C%20basement%20apartments%2C%20or%20converted%20garages%20%E2%80%94%20offer%20smaller%2C%20cheaper%20housing%20options%2C%20particularly%20in%20expensive%20neighborhoods%20dominated%20by%20single-family%20houses.%20They've%20also%20been%20embraced%20by%20homeowners%20looking%20to%20boost%20their%20property%20values%20and%20earn%20income%20by%20renting%20out%20their%20extra%20units.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20York%20City's%20legalization%20of%20ADUs%20for%20thousands%20of%20homeowners%20went%20into%20effect%20this%20week%2C%20so%20we%20looked%20at%20how%20ADUs%20have%20helped%20homeowners%20and%20renters%20in%20other%20places%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Real%20estate%20developer%20Scott%20Turner%20stands%20in%20front%20of%20the%20four%20homes%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0including%20two%201%2C000-square-foot%20ADUs%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0that%20he%20built%20in%20south%20central%20Austin.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660dcd6016bde8d4ead57650%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22850%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EReal%20estate%20developer%20Scott%20Turner%20stands%20in%20front%20of%20the%20four%20homes%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0including%20two%201%2C000-square-foot%20ADUs%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0that%20he%20built%20in%20south%20central%20Austin.%3Cp%3EEliza%20Relman%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22827390a9-1e78-4fe6-bd77-ff03805d9045%5C%22%3EThe%20pros%20and%20cons%20of%20ADUs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20benefits%20of%20ADUs%20start%20with%20affordability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20median%20rent%20for%20a%20California%20ADU%20costs%20less%20than%2030%25%20of%20the%20median%20income%20of%20two-person%20households%20in%20the%20greater%20San%20Francisco%20Bay%20region%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aducalifornia.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2FImplementing-the-Backyard-Revolution.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2021%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20the%20state's%20ADUs%20were%20affordable%20to%20people%20making%20less%20than%2080%25%20of%20their%20local%20median%20income.%20Nearly%20half%20of%20California%20ADU%20owners%20said%20they've%20rented%20out%20their%20unit%20to%20short-%20or%20long-term%20tenants%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvillahomes.com%2Fblog%2Fadu-rental-income-survey%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20poll%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EADUs%20create%20opportunities%20for%20multiple%20generations%20of%20a%20family%20to%20live%20together%2C%20as%20they're%20often%20used%20to%20house%20aging%20parents%20or%20grandparents%2C%20or%20adult%20children.%20According%20to%20the%20poll%20of%20California%20ADU%20owners%2C%2061%25%20said%20they%20built%20their%20ADU%20to%20house%20a%20family%20member.%20ADUs%20are%20also%20often%20designed%20to%20be%20more%20accessible%20for%20those%20with%20limited%20mobility%20than%20other%20kinds%20of%20housing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EADUs%20also%20help%20homeowners%20boost%20their%20property%20values%20and%20bring%20in%20a%20new%20source%20of%20income.%20In%20the%20biggest%20cities%2C%20the%20addition%20of%20an%20ADU%20increases%20a%20property's%20value%20by%20an%20average%20of%2035%25%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nar.realtor%2Fmagazine%2Freal-estate-news%2Fstudy-adus-can-add-35-to-home-s-value%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%202021%20study%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESelma%20Hepp%2C%20chief%20economist%20at%20the%20property%20information%20and%20analytics%20firm%20CoreLogic%2C%20converted%20her%20backyard%20garage%20into%20a%20500-square-foot%20studio%20apartment%20that%20she%20rents%20out%20on%20Airbnb.%20Hepp%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconvert-garage-into-airbnb-rent-pay-mortgage-california-adu-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Business%20Insider%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20she%20brought%20in%20about%20%243%2C000%20per%20month%20in%20income%20from%20the%20ADU%20%E2%80%94%20enough%20to%20cover%20the%20monthly%20mortgage%20payments%20on%20her%20primary%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDevelopers%20have%20also%20taken%20advantage%20of%20ADU%20legalization%20to%20build%20more%20density.%20In%20Austin%2C%20Texas%2C%20real-estate%20developer%20Scott%20Turner%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faustin-housing-market-real-estate-prices-rent-multi-unit-adus-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereplaced%20a%20single-family%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20a%20large%20corner%20lot%20with%20two%20single-family%20homes%20and%20two%20ADUs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20ADUs%20can%20be%20costly%20to%20build.%20Construction%20typically%20runs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.angi.com%2Farticles%2Fhow-much-do-adu-costs.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebetween%20%2460%2C000%20and%20%24285%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E.%20On%20top%20of%20that%2C%20local%20regulations%20can%20slow%20down%20the%20approval%20and%20construction%20process%2C%20further%20raising%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20a%20real-estate%20industry%20professional%2C%20Hepp%20struggled%20to%20sort%20out%20the%20rules%20and%20regulations%20on%20ADU%20construction%20in%20LA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20very%20stressful%20because%20every%20step%20of%20the%20way%2C%20I%20needed%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20the%20next%20step%20was%2C%20and%20it%20was%20sort%20of%20hard%20to%20get%20a%20straight%20answer%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Outside%20Selma%20Hepp's%20ADU%20in%20Burbank%2C%20California.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ecefd015cc5d00198c783f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOutside%20Selma%20Hepp's%20ADU%20in%20Burbank%2C%20California.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Selma%20Hepp%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a2c2017f-5394-4722-8564-87d847d287eb%5C%22%3EStates%20jump%20on%20the%20ADU%20bandwagon%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mercatus.org%2Fresearch%2Fpolicy-briefs%2Ftaxonomy-state-accessory-dwelling-unit-laws-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFourteen%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20the%20country%20have%20legalized%20ADUs.%20California%20led%20the%20charge%20and%20has%20passed%20a%20series%20of%20laws%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadu-tiny-homes-affordable-housing-california-laws-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpanding%20and%20standardizing%20ADUs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%2C%C2%A0in%20some%20cases%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-to-pay-homeowners-to-build-adu-housing-shortage-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehelping%20pay%20for%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0their%20construction.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fcalifornia%2Fstory%2F2024-06-14%2Fsan-jose-allows-homeowers-to-sell-adus-separately%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMore%20than%2060%2C000%20ADUs%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20permitted%20across%20the%20state%20since%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOregon%20and%20Washington%20have%20similarly%20seen%20spikes%20in%20ADU%20construction%20since%20liberalizing%20their%20laws.%20New%20York%20and%20Vermont%20have%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstates-will-compensate-you-for-building-tiny-home-adu-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoffered%20subsidies%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20some%20homeowners%20to%20build%20ADUs.%20Freddie%20Mac%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.freddiemac.com%2Fresearch%2Finsight%2F20200716-identifying-accessory-dwelling-units-from-real-estate%3Futm_medium%3Dwebsite%26utm_source%3Darchdaily.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%20in%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20number%20of%20homes%20with%20ADUs%20in%20the%20US%20grew%20from%201.1%20million%20in%202000%20to%20more%20than%2010%20million%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20since%20most%20ADU%20legalization%20efforts%20have%20happened%20since%202022%2C%20their%20full%20effects%20are%20not%20yet%20evident%20in%20many%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20ADU%20legalization%20alone%20isn't%20usually%20enough%20to%20prompt%20lots%20of%20new%20construction.%20In%20some%20cities%20and%20towns%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mercatus.org%2Fresearch%2Fpolicy-briefs%2Ftaxonomy-state-accessory-dwelling-unit-laws-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elocal%20land-use%20laws%2C%20permitting%2C%20and%20other%20regulations%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20stood%20in%20the%20way.%20Owner-occupancy%20requirements%2C%20off-street%20parking%20mandates%2C%20and%20discretionary%20permit%20reviews%20are%20among%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mercatus.org%2Fresearch%2Fpolicy-briefs%2Ftaxonomy-state-accessory-dwelling-unit-laws-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20burdensome%20rules%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20homeowners%20have%20successfully%20fought%20the%20regulations.%20Malibu%20homeowners%20Jason%20and%20Elizabeth%20Riddick%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmalibu-suing-homeowners-california-supreme-court-backyard-tiny-home-adu-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efought%20a%20multi-year%20legal%20battle%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20their%20city%20over%20their%20plan%20to%20build%20a%20460-square-foot%20ADU%20on%20their%20property.%20The%20couple%20ultimately%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmalibutimes.com%2Friddick-family-prevails-in-adu-suit-against-the-city-of-malibu%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprevailed%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20Elizabeth%20Riddick%20insisted%20that%20the%20city%20is%20%26quot%3Bnot%20interested%20in%20supporting%20any%20type%20of%20additional%20housing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20ADUs%20catch%20on%2C%20pro-housing%20policymakers%20and%20experts%20say%20the%20incremental%20approach%20to%20building%20more%20homes%20is%20a%20first%20step%20towards%20solving%20the%20nation's%20housing%20shortage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENolan%20Gray%2C%20the%20research%20director%20at%20California%20YIMBY%2C%20called%20ADU%20legalization%20%26quot%3Bthe%20beachhead%20for%20broader%20reform%26quot%3B%20of%20housing%20policy%20because%20backyard%20homes%20tend%20to%20be%20popular%20with%20homeowners%20who've%20otherwise%20resisted%20new%20housing%20in%20their%20neighborhoods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20start%20to%20de-normalize%20this%20idea%20that%2075%25%20to%2090%25%20of%20the%20typical%20American%20city%20is