rc%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67532be68fbb2783ed30482e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20man%20plays%20board%20games%20with%20his%20son%20and%20his%20father.%3Cp%3EMaskot%2FGetty%20Images%2FMaskot%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMany%20Gen%20Xers%20are%20caring%20for%20both%20their%20children%20and%20parents%2C%20and%20it's%20hurting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Faverage-401k-balance%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%20savings%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E56%25%20of%20Gen%20X%20investors%20were%20financially%20supporting%20either%20their%20parents%20or%20their%20kids%2C%20Nationwide%20found.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20financial%20burden%20of%20supporting%20two%20groups%20has%20some%20Gen%20Xers%20doubting%20if%20they'll%20retire%20at%20all.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESteve%20Mullen%2C%2054%2C%20is%20being%20pulled%20three%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20he%20and%20his%20wife%20are%20caregivers%20for%20each%20of%20their%20mothers%2C%20which%20has%20required%20them%20to%20pitch%20in%20up%20to%2040%20hours%20of%20caregiving%20a%20week%20and%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20over%20the%20course%20of%20decades.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20they%20are%20still%20supporting%20their%20college-age%20son%2C%20who%20needs%20help%20with%20housing%20and%20%2425%2C000%20for%20tuition%20every%20year.%20All%20the%20while%2C%20he%20runs%20his%20own%20PR%20business%2C%20in%20which%20making%20more%20money%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bconstant%26quot%3B%20concern.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20times%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20burden%20is%20extraordinary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20incredibly%20stressful%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20adding%20that%20money%20was%20always%20a%20back-of-mind%20worry%2C%20despite%20being%20relatively%20financially%20stable.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20pray%20we%20don't%20go%20into%20another%20one%20of%20these%20periods%20where%20my%20mother's%20in%20the%20hospital.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20situation%20is%20becoming%20increasingly%20common%20among%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-savings-crisis-gen-x-boomers-social-security-401k-pensions-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Xers%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20generation%20sandwiched%20between%20their%20retiring%20parents%20and%20still-dependent%20children%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20more%20frequently%2C%20needing%20to%20support%20both%20groups%20at%20once.%20It%20is%20a%20dilemma%20that%20has%20put%20Gen%20X%20further%20behind%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fretirement-planning%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaving%20for%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E%20compared%20to%20other%20groups%2C%20financial%20planning%20experts%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20signs%20that%20the%20dual%20burden%20of%20needing%20to%20support%20kids%20and%20parents%20is%20becoming%20more%20common.%20A%202020%20study%20from%20the%20AARP%20and%20the%20National%20Alliance%20for%20Caregiving%20found%20that%20among%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aarp.org%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Faarp%2Fppi%2F2020%2F05%2Fgeneration-x-caregiver.doi.10.26419-2Fppi.00103.009.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Xers%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0who%20are%20taking%20care%20of%20a%20parent%2C%20around%2050%25%20also%20have%20a%20child%20under%20the%20age%20of%2018.%20A%20study%20conducted%20by%20Nationwide%20showed%20that%2056%25%20are%20financially%20supporting%20either%20their%20parents%20or%20their%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Xers%20in%20caretaking%20roles%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20show%20signs%20of%20financial%20strain.%20Of%20those%20who%20were%20taking%20care%20of%20a%20child%20or%20a%20parent%2C%2021%25%20said%20they%20had%20taken%20out%20significant%20amounts%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-x-charts-show-struggles-bills-spending-need-more-work-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edebt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%2020%25%20said%20they%20were%20unable%20to%20save%20for%20retirement%2C%20per%20the%20Nationwide%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20separate%20survey%20of%2035-%20to%2060-year-olds%20conducted%20by%20Carewell%2C%2075%25%20of%20those%20taking%20care%20of%20both%20a%20parent%20and%20a%20child%20said%20they%20struggled%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fretirement-planning%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esave%20for%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%2063%25%20said%20they%20lived%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Xers%20speaking%20with%20BI%20said%20they%20doubted%20if%20they%20would%20ever%20retire%2C%20mostly%20because%20they%20were%20set%20back%20by%20financial%20obligations%20related%20to%20caregiving.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E40%25%20of%20Gen%20Xers%20also%20expect%20to%20work%20part-time%20after%20they%20retire%2C%20a%20Prudential%20Financial%20survey%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJulie%2C%20a%20woman%20in%20her%20fifties%20based%20in%20Ohio%2C%20said%20she%20had%20spent%20over%20%24100%2C000%20taking%20care%20of%20her%20mother%20over%20the%20course%20of%2015%20years.%20She%20has%20less%20than%20%2470%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fhow-much-do-i-need-to-retire%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaved%20for%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20well%20below%20what's%20recommended%20by%20financial%20advisors%2C%20who%20say%20you%20should%20have%20around%20six%20times%20your%20annual%20salary%20saved%20by%20the%20time%20you%20hit%2050.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20exhausted%20financially%2C%20and%2C%20frankly%2C%20I%20didn't%20consider%20growing%20up%20I'd%20be%20the%20financial%20rock%20of%20my%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.