that%20Kyiv%20was%20involved%20in%20the%20fighting%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETykhyi%20was%20responding%20to%20a%20question%20about%20accusations%20from%20Iran%2C%20another%20ally%20of%20Assad%2C%20that%20Ukraine%20was%20supporting%20what%20Tehran%20called%20terrorist%20groups.%20%26quot%3BUkraine%20categorically%20and%20decisively%20rejects%20any%20accusations%20...%20about%20our%20supposed%20involvement%20in%20the%20deteriorating%20security%20situation%20in%20Syria%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRussia's%20significant%20losses%20in%20Ukraine%20have%20led%20Moscow%20to%20withdraw%20the%20majority%20of%20its%20troops%20and%20equipment%20from%20Syria%2C%20leaving%20its%20ally%20...%20without%20the%20necessary%20support%2C%26quot%3B%20Tykhyi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFall%20Of%20Syria%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20peak%20of%20the%20conflict%20in%20Syria%20nearly%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20Aleppo%20was%20at%20the%20frontlines%20of%20the%20war%20between%20government-controlled%20and%20rebel%20forces.%20However%2C%20with%20the%20help%20of%20Russian%20airpower%20and%20the%20Lebanon-based%20militant%20group%20Hezbollah%2C%20President%20Bashar%20al-Assad%20was%20able%20to%20regain%20control%20over%20the%20entire%20Aleppo%20by%20the%20end%20of%202016.%20Since%20then%2C%20conflict%20in%20Syria%20has%20been%20majorly%20static%20with%20the%20rebels%20largely%20confined%20to%20the%20Idlib%20governate%2C%20adjacent%20to%20the%20Aleppo%20governate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20after%20years%20locked%20behind%20frozen%20frontlines%2C%20Syrian%20rebels%20have%20burst%20forth%20to%20mount%20the%20swiftest%20battlefield%20advance%20by%20either%20side%20since%20a%20rebellion%20against%20President%20Assad%20descended%20into%20civil%20war%2013%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Assad%2C%20who%20had%20crushed%20all%20forms%20of%20dissent%2C%20flew%20out%20of%20Damascus%20for%20an%20unknown%20destination%20earlier%20on%20Sunday%2C%20two%20senior%20army%20officers%20told%20Reuters%2C%20as%20rebels%20said%20they%20had%20entered%20the%20capital%20with%20no%20sign%20of%20army%20deployments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAfter%2050%20years%20of%20oppression%20under%20Baath%20rule%2C%20and%2013%20years%20of%20crimes%20and%20tyranny%20and%20(forced)%20displacement...%20we%20announce%20today%20the%20end%20of%20this%20dark%20period%20and%20the%20start%20of%20a%20new%20era%20for%20Syria%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20rebel%20factions%20said%20on%20Telegram.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Syrian%20army%20later%20said%20it%20was%20continuing%20operations%20against%20%26quot%3Bterrorist%20groups%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20key%20cities%20of%20Hama%20and%20Homs%20and%20in%20Deraa%20countryside.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pace%20of%20events%20in%20Syria%20has%20stunned%20Arab%20capitals%20and%20raised%20fears%20of%20a%20new%20wave%20of%20regional%20instability.%C2%A0Clearly%2C%20the%20armed%20opposition%20forces%20took%20advantage%20of%20the%20change%20in%20the%20power%20balance%20caused%20by%20nearby%20wars--%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20in%20Lebanon%20and%20the%20Middle%20East.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael's%20war%20in%20Gaza%20and%20Lebanon%20has%20done%20significant%20damage%20to%20Mr%20Asaad's%20ally%20Iran's%20so-called%20axis%20of%20resistance%2C%20especially%20Hezbollah.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Russia%2C%20another%20stakeholder%20in%20Syria%2C%20is%20distracted%20by%20its%20fight%20in%20Ukraine%20making%20it%20harder%20to%20defend%20the%20Assad%20regime.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERussia's%20Stake%20In%20Syria%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lightning%20advance%20of%20rebels%20in%20Syria%20is%20threatening%20one%20of%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin's%20proudest%20achievements%2C%20his%202015%20military%20intervention%20to%20save%20Bashar%20al-Assad's%20regime.%20The%20end%20of%20Mr%20Asaad's%20control%20in%20Syria%20risks%20not%20just%20Russia's%20prestige%2C%20but%20its%20coveted%20military%20foothold%20in%20the%20eastern%20Mediterranean%20region--%20the%20naval%20base%20of%20Tartus%20and%2C%20further%20north%2C%20the%20Hmeimim%20Air%20Base%2C%20both%20with%2049-year-leases%20received%20after%20Russia's%20regime-saving%20intervention%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2024%2F12%2F06%2Frussia-syria-war-rebels-tartus-bases%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20using%20these%20bases%20to%20protect%20Mr%20Assad's%20fragile%20regime%2C%20Moscow%20has%20used%20them%20to%20challenge%20American%20supremacy%20by%20projecting%20its%20military%20power%20in%20the%20eastern%20Mediterranean%20and%20claiming%20the%20role%20of%20a%20world%20power%20with%20vital%20regional%20interests.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%2C%20however%2C%20currently%20has%20its%20hands%20full%20with%20its%20war%20on%20Ukraine.%20As%20per%20an%20estimate%20by%20Britain's%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%2C%20November%20was%20the%20costliest%20month%20of%20the%20war%20so%20far%20for%20Moscow's%20forces%2C%20with%20an%20average%20of%20more%20than%201%2C500%20killed%20or%20wounded%20a%20day.%20Russia%20has%20been%20facing%20a%20Ukrainian%20incursion%20on%20its%20own%20soil%20since%20August%20that%20it%20is%20struggling%20to%20expel%2C%20now%20with%20the%20help%20of%20North%20Korean%20soldiers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20amid%20the%20reports%20of%20the%20fall%20of%20Syria%2C%20Russia%20is%20at%20risk%20of%20losing%20control%20over%20the%20Hmeimim%20and%20Tartus%20bases.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Could%20Fall%20Of%20Syria%20Impact%20Russia's%20War%20In%20Ukraine%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20report%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkyivindependent.com%2Ffall-of-aleppo-deals-blow-to-russias-middle-east-clout-may-indirectly-strengthen-ukraines-hand%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Kyiv%20Independent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Charles%20Lister%2C%20a%20Syria%20expert%20at%20the%20Middle%20East%20Institute%20said%20even%20during%20the%20war%20on%20Ukraine%2C%20Moscow%20never%20scaled%20its%20military%20presence%20back%20down.%20However%2C%20the%20quality%20of%20Russia's%20officer%20corps%20in%20Syria%20had%20declined.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRussia%20retains%20exactly%20the%20same%20troop%20levels.%20They've%20conducted%20the%20same%20number%20of%20air%20sorties%20over%20Syria%20with%20the%20same%20geographical%20breadth%20that%20they%20did%20prior%20to%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20speaking%20on%20the%20Lawfare%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20has%20changed%2C%20however%2C%20is%20that%20Russia%20can%20no%20longer%20count%20on%20the%20Wagner%20Group%2C%20which%20has%20played%20a%20significant%20role%20in%20safeguarding%20the%20Kremlin's%20interests%20in%20Syria%20in%20the%20past.%20Bogged%20down%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20Russia%20cannot%20send%20serious%20reinforcements%20to%20its%20military%20contingent%20in%20the%20Middle%20Eastern%20country%20either%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lowyinstitute.org%2Fthe-interpreter%2Frussia-loser-fall-syria-s-aleppo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Interpreter.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20its%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20Kremlin%20has%20lost%20several%20allies%20from%20the%20Collective%20Security%20Treaty%20Organisation%20(CSTO).%20The%20end%20of%20Mr%20Asaad's%20regime%20could%20mean%20Russia%20loses%20Syria%20as%20well%2C%20forcing%20the%20Kremlin%20to%20eventually%20shut%20down%20its%20Khmeimim%20Air%20Base%20in%20the%20Latakia%20area%2C%20and%20the%20naval%20facility%20in%20Tartus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20two%20years%20of%20war%2C%20Moscow%20has%20redeployed%20weaponry%20from%20Syria%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20including%20Pantsir%20missile%20systems.%20Exposing%20its%20military%20and%20political%20weakness%20in%20Syria%20could%20undermine%20Russia's%20leverage%20in%20any%20potential%20negotiations%20surrounding%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fall%20of%20Aleppo%20has%20exposed%20the%20Kremlin%20to%20the%20risk%20of%20military%20overreach%20and%20has%20put%20its%20alliance%20with%20Iran%20under%20stress%20because%20of%20its%20competing%20military%20objectives%20in%20the%20country%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.euronews.com%2F2024%2F12%2F04%2Fsyria-how-the-conflict-could-impact-the-ukraine-crisis-and-migration%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEuro%20News%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%20is%20thus%20keen%20on%20encouraging%20dialogue%20between%20Ankara%20and%20Damascus%20and%20has%20deployed%20diplomatic%20efforts%20to%20open%20trilateral%20negotiations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733645100000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2F61kuovo_syria-civil-war-afp_625x300_08_December_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fas-syrian-rebels-topple-assad-regime-how-it-may-impact-russia-ukrainewar-7199697%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20five%20decades%20of%20Baath%20rule%20in%20Syria%20ended%20on%20Sunday%20as%20Islamist-led%20rebels%20declared%20that%20they%20had%20taken%20Damascus%2C%20sending%20President%20Bashar%20al-Assad%20fleeing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fas-syrian-rebels-topple-assad-regime-how-it-may-impact-russia-ukrainewar-7199697%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2220-year-old%20Punjab%20student%20working%20as%20security%20guard%20shot%20dead%20in%20Canada%22%2