0decade%20of%20brutal%20civil%20war.%20Rebel%20groups%2C%20including%20Hayat%20Tahrir%20al-Sham%2C%20have%20made%20significant%20advances%2C%20leaving%20the%20capital%20vulnerable%20and%20marking%20the%20collapse%20of%20Assad's%20once%20impenetrable%20government.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20capital%2C%20now%20left%20vulnerable%2C%20stands%20as%20a%20symbol%20of%20the%20regime's%20sudden%20fall.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20shifting%20power%20dynamics%20reflect%20the%20unravelling%20of%20a%20family%20dynasty%20that%20has%20defined%20Syria's%20fate%20for%20over%20half%20a%20century.%20Bashar%20Al-Assad%20was%20the%20%26quot%3Blast%20standing%26quot%3B.%20Often%20called%20%26quot%3Ba%20dictator%20without%20a%20dictator%2C%26quot%3B%20his%20power%20relied%20not%20just%20on%20his%20leadership%2C%20but%20on%20the%20unyielding%20support%20of%20his%20%26quot%3Binner%20circle%26quot%3B%2C%20his%20closest%20family%20members%20-%20his%20brother%20Maher%2C%20a%20fiery%20military%20commander%3B%20his%20sister%20Bushra%2C%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Iron%20Lady%26quot%3B%3B%20and%20her%20husband%20Asef%20Shawkat%2C%20a%20calculating%20intelligence%20figure.%20But%20as%20Assad%20flees%2C%20their%20once-unified%20front%20begins%20to%20fracture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20closer%20look%20at%20the%20key%20players%20within%20the%20regime's%20inner%20circle%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaher%20Al-Assad%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFifty-six-year-old%20Maher%20al-Assad%2C%20Bashar's%20younger%20brother%2C%20commands%20Syria's%20Republican%20Guard%20and%20the%204th%20Armoured%20Division%2C%20making%20him%20a%20key%20figure%20in%20both%20Syria's%20military%20and%20its%20alliance%20with%20Iran.%20Known%20as%20the%20hardliner%20of%20the%20family%2C%20Maher%20is%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20ruthless%20face%20of%20power%26quot%3B%20and%20oversees%20the%20Shabiha%20militia%2C%20which%20protects%20the%20Assad%20regime's%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESanctioned%20by%20the%20EU%20in%202011%20for%20his%20role%20in%20violence%20against%20protesters%2C%20Maher's%20reputation%20for%20cruelty%20is%20reflected%20in%20protests%20that%20often%20target%20him%20directly.%20He%20has%20also%20been%20linked%20to%20the%201999%20shooting%20of%20his%20brother-in-law%2C%20Asef%20Shawkat%2C%20and%20named%20a%20suspect%20in%20the%202005%20assassination%20of%20Lebanese%20prime%20minister%20Rafik%20Hariri.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnisa%20Makhlouf%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnisa%20Makhlouf%2C%20widow%20of%20the%20late%20Syrian%20President%20Hafez%20al-Assad%20and%20mother%20of%20Bashar%2C%20may%20keep%20a%20low%20profile%2C%20but%20she%20holds%20the%20final%20say%20on%20all%20matters%20within%20the%20Assad%20family.%20%26quot%3BDecisions%20are%20made%20collectively%20in%20the%20family's%20inner%20circle%2C%20but%20Anisa%20has%20the%20last%20say%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Wael%20al-Hafez%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Syrian%20opposition%20in%20exile%2C%20according%20to%20the%20feminist%20blog%20Les%20Martiennes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBushra%20Al-Assad%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%201960%2C%20Bushra%20Al-Assad%20is%20Bashar's%20only%20sister%20and%20a%20trained%20pharmacist.%20Like%20her%20brother%20Maher%2C%20she%20is%20known%20as%20a%20hawk%20within%20the%20regime%20and%20plays%20a%20significant%20role%20as%20Bashar's%20secretary.%20In%20the%20mid-1990s%2C%20she%20married%20Asef%20Shawkat.%20Bushra%20has%20also%20had%20a%20strained%20relationship%20with%20Bashar's%20wife%2C%20Asma.%20According%20to%20former%20Syrian%20diplomat%20Mohammed%20Daoud%2C%20Bushra%20long%20prevented%20Asma%20from%20assuming%20the%20title%20of%20Syria's%20%26quot%3BFirst%20Lady%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20title%20she%20preferred%20to%20keep%20with%20her%20mother%2C%20Anisa.%20She%20has%20business%20ties%20with%20Rami%20Makhlouf%2C%20Bashar's%20maternal%20cousin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERami%20Makhlouf%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERami%20Makhlouf%2C%20Bashar%20al-Assad's%20first%20cousin%2C%20controls%20about%2060%20per%20cent%20of%20Syria's%20business.%20Born%20in%201965%2C%20he's%20considered%20Syria's%20richest%20man%2C%20with%20interests%20in%20telecommunications%2C%20retail%2C%20energy%2C%20banking%2C%20and%20transportation.%20The%20US%20sanctioned%20him%20in%202008%20for%20abusing%20political%20influence%2C%20and%20the%20EU%20followed%20in%202011%2C%20accusing%20him%20of%20funding%20the%20crackdown%20on%20protesters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHated%20for%20corruption%2C%20Rami%20Makhlouf%20recently%20announced%20plans%20to%20donate%20part%20of%20his%20fortune%20to%20charity.%20His%20brother%2C%20Hafez%20Makhlouf%2C%20heads%20Syria's%20civilian%20intelligence%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAsef%20Shawkat%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeneral%20Asef%20Shawkat%2C%20an%20Alawite%20military%20officer%2C%20married%20Bashar%20al-Assad's%20sister%2C%20Bushra%2C%20in%201995.%20Initially%20rejected%20by%20the%20Assad%20family%2C%20he%20eventually%20gained%20their%20trust%20and%20built%20a%20close%20relationship%20with%20Bashar.%20Asef%20Shawkat%20quickly%20rose%20through%20the%20ranks%2C%20serving%20as%20Head%20of%20Military%20Intelligence%2C%20then%20Deputy%20Military%20Intelligence%20Chief%2C%20and%20later%20Chief%20of%20Military%20Intelligence%20until%202005.%20Despite%20facing%20international%20controversies%2C%20he%20was%20reassigned%20as%20Deputy%20Chief-of-Staff%20in%202008.%20He%2C%20along%20with%20Maher%20al-Assad%2C%20is%20linked%20to%20the%202005%20assassination%20of%20Lebanese%20Prime%20Minister%20Rafik%20Hariri.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAsma%20Al-Assad%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%20London%20in%201975%20to%20a%20Syrian%20diplomat%20family%2C%20Asma%20Al-Assad%20married%20Bashar%20al-Assad%20in%20December%202000.%20The%20couple%20has%20three%20sons%3A%20Hafez%2C%20Zein%2C%20and%20Karim.%20Asma%20holds%20degrees%20in%20computer%20science%20and%20F