0from%20their%20historically%20marginalised%20status%2C%20as%20the%20Alawites%20began%20to%20assert%20influence%20within%20Syria's%20evolving%20power%20structures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Alawite%20minority%2C%20which%20makes%20up%20roughly%2012-15%20per%20cent%20of%20Syria's%20pre-war%20population%2C%20has%20been%20the%20regime's%20primary%20base%20of%20support.%20This%20loyalty%20stems%20in%20part%20from%20the%20community's%20historical%20marginalisation%20and%20the%20opportunities%20afforded%20to%20them%20under%20the%20Assads%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20military%20and%20security%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsyria-war-bashar-al-assad-syrian-rebels-beseige-damascus-assad-regime-braces-for-last-stand-7198085%23pfrom%3Dhome-ndtv_topscroll%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESyrian%20Rebels%20Enter%20Damascus%2C%20US%20Fears%20President%20Assad's%20Chemical%20Weapons%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlawites%2C%20while%20not%20doctrinally%20Shia%2C%20venerate%20Ali%20ibn%20Abi%20Talib%2C%20a%20figure%20central%20to%20Shia%20Islam.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Baath%20Party%2C%20established%20in%201947%2C%20%C2%A0sought%20to%20unite%20Arab%20nationalism%2C%20socialism%2C%20secularism%2C%20and%20anti-imperialism.%20For%20many%20Alawites%2C%20the%20Baath%20Party's%20secular%20and%20inclusive%20ideals%20offered%20a%20more%20appealing%20alternative%20to%20the%20Muslim%20Brotherhood%2C%20a%20Sunni%20Islamist%20organisation%20founded%20in%20Egypt%20that%20had%20garnered%20a%20considerable%20following%20in%20Syria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Dynasty%20By%20Design%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHafez%20al-Assad%20intended%20to%20pass%20his%20legacy%20to%20his%20eldest%20son%2C%20Bassel%2C%20who%20was%20groomed%20for%20leadership.%20However%2C%20Bassel's%20untimely%20death%20in%20a%20car%20accident%20in%201994%20forced%20Hafez%20to%20turn%20to%20his%20second%20son%2C%20Bashar%2C%20a%20relatively%20inexperienced%20ophthalmologist.%20When%20Hafez%20died%20in%202000%2C%20Bashar%20assumed%20the%20presidency%2C%20confirmed%20in%20office%20by%20a%20referendum%20that%20secured%2097%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20vote%20-%20a%20predictable%20outcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBashar's%20ascent%20was%20initially%20met%20with%20optimism.%20Many%20Syrians%20and%20foreign%20observers%20hoped%20he%20would%20bring%20reforms%20and%20openness%20to%20a%20system%20long%20stifled%20by%20authoritarian%20rule.%20However%2C%20those%20hopes%20quickly%20dissipated.%20Bashar%20inherited%20not%20only%20his%20father's%20system%20but%20also%20his%20father's%20inner%20circle%2C%20composed%20of%20ageing%20revolutionary%20leaders%20who%20had%20controlled%20key%20state%20institutions%20since%20the%201970s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBashar's%20Consolidation%20Of%20Power%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBashar's%20early%20years%20in%20power%20were%20marked%20by%20attempts%20to%20replace%20his%20father's%20allies%20with%20his%20own%20confidants%2C%20most%20of%20whom%20belonged%20to%20Syria's%20urban%20elite.%20Unlike%20their%20predecessors%2C%20Bashar's%20inner%20circle%20had%20no%20grassroots%20connections%2C%20isolating%20the%20regime%20from%20Syria's%20rural%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20weakening%20of%20state%20institutions%20under%20Bashar%20coincided%20with%20the%20rise%20of%20a%20narrow%20clique%20of%20elites%20centred%20around%20his%20family.%20Figures%20such%20as%20his%20brother%20Maher%2C%20his%20sister%20Bushra%2C%20and%20her%20husband%20Asef%20Shawkat%20played%20key%20roles%20in%20the%20regime's%20security%20and%20military%20apparatus.%20Economic%20power%20was%20concentrated%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20regime%20cronies%2C%20most%20notably%20Rami%20Makhlouf%2C%20Bashar's%20cousin%2C%20who%20reportedly%20controlled%20more%20than%2060%20per%20cent%20of%20Syria's%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%7C%20