%20%26quot%3BThe%20situation%20was%20not%20like%20this%20when%20I%20left%20my%20house%20this%20morning...%20suddenly%20everyone%20was%20scared%2C%26quot%3B%20Rania%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20afraid%20because%20we%20really%20don't%20know%20what's%20going%20to%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20resident%2C%20Shahla%2C%20told%20BBC.%20%26quot%3BNobody%20wants%20to%20see%20fighting%20in%20Damascus.%20Everything%20is%20ambiguous%20and%20nothing%20is%20clear%20for%20anyone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERim%20Turkmani%2C%20director%20of%20Syria%20Conflict%20Research%20Programme%20at%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%2C%20told%20BBC%20that%20her%20sister%20in%20Damascus%20told%20her%20that%20shops%20were%20closing%20down%2C%20supplies%20were%20running%20low%20and%20ATMs%20were%20out%20of%20cash.%20%26quot%3BNo%20one%20knows%20what's%20happening%2C%26quot%3B%20Ms%20Turkmani%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20an%20Al%20Jazeera%20correspondent%20spoke%20to%20people%20on%20the%20streets%2C%20they%20welcomed%20the%20rebel%20forces'%20win.%20Slamming%20the%20Bashar%20Al-Assad%20regime%2C%20one%20of%20them%20said%20it%20was%20forcing%20young%20men%20to%20join%20the%20Army%20and%20many%20people%20fled%20to%20Lebanon%20because%20they%20did%20not%20want%20to%20fight%20their%20fellow%20Syrians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20overthrow%20of%20the%20Bashar%20al-Assad%20regime%20follows%20a%2013-year%20rebellion%20that%20started%20as%20a%20peaceful%20uprising%20against%20President%20Assad%20and%20snowballed%20into%20a%20full-scale%20civil%20war%20that%20devastated%20Syria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHayat%20Tahrir%20al-Sham%2C%20which%20led%20the%20offensive%2C%20was%20formed%20in%202012%20under%20the%20name%20of%20al-Nusra.%20It%20pledged%20allegiance%20to%20al-Qaeda%20the%20next%20year.%20In%202016%2C%20however%2C%20it%20broke%20ties%20with%20al-Qaeda%20and%20took%20the%20name%20Hayat%20Tahrir%20al-Sham.%20Global%20powers%2C%20including%20the%20US%20and%20the%20U