225086%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22TikTok%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6754aaf54adc4cc1343536b1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223377%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20federal%20appeals%20court%20upheld%20a%20law%20that%20could%20ban%20TikTok%20in%20the%20United%20States%20as%20constitutional.%3Cp%3Ecredit%20should%20read%20CFOTO%2FFuture%20Publishing%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20court%20that%20upheld%20a%20law%20that%20could%20ban%20TikTok%20said%20the%20US%20showed%20no%20evidence%20China%20manipulates%20content.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHowever%2C%20the%20court%20said%20TikTok%20has%20manipulated%20content%20at%20China's%20request%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETikTok%20denies%20content%20manipulation%20and%20says%20it%20expects%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20reverse%20the%20ban.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20appeals%20court%20that%20upheld%20a%20law%20that%20could%20ban%20TikTok%20in%20the%20United%20States%20said%20the%20government%20offered%20no%20evidence%20that%20China%20is%20manipulating%20content%20on%20the%20platform%20in%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20panel%20of%20judges%20wrote%20in%20their%20opinion%20that%20evidence%20that%20China%20has%20compelled%20TikTok%20to%20manipulate%20content%20elsewhere%20was%20enough%20for%20it%20to%20uphold%20a%20federal%20law%20signed%20by%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20that%20would%20force%20TikTok's%20sale%20in%20the%20United%20States%20to%20an%20American%20company%20or%20ban%20it%20from%20app%20stores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20District%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20of%20the%20District%20of%20Columbia%20found%20on%20Friday%20in%20a%20majority%20opinion%20that%20the%20federal%20law%20is%20constitutional.%20The%20law%2C%20which%20was%20passed%20in%20April%2C%20requires%20TikTok's%20Chinese%20parent%20company%2C%20Bytedance%2C%20to%20divest%20from%20the%20company%20by%20January%2019%20or%20face%20a%20ban%20in%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20officials%20across%20political%20lines%20have%20worried%20that%20TikTok%20poses%20a%20national%20security%20risk%20because%20of%20its%20Chinese%20ownership.%20Some%20members%20of%20Congress%20have%20said%20they%20fear%20that%20TikTok%20could%20be%20used%20as%20a%20propaganda%20tool%20to%20push%20narratives%20favorable%20to%20China's%20Communist%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20statements%20supporting%20the%20bill%2C%20Democratic%20Massachusetts%20Rep.%20Jake%20Auchincloss%20called%20TikTok%20%26quot%3Ba%20tool%20of%20censorship%20and%20propaganda%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%2C%20and%20Republican%20Nebraska%20Rep.%20Mike%20Flood%20said%20the%20app%20has%20%26quot%3Bbeen%20used%20as%20a%20tool%20of%20propaganda%20in%20our%20country.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20federal%20appeals%20court%20wrote%20in%20its%20majority%20opinion%20that%20the%20government%20did%20not%20present%20any%20evidence%20that%20China%20has%20tried%20to%20manipulate%20content%20on%20TikTok%20in%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Government%20acknowledges%20that%20it%20lacks%20specific%20intelligence%20that%20shows%20the%20PRC%20has%20in%20the%20past%20or%20is%20now%20coercing%20TikTok%20into%20manipulating%20content%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20opinion%20says%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20People's%20Republic%20of%20China.%20However%2C%20the%20government%20argued%20in%20court%20that%20ByteDance%20and%20TikTok%20have%20censored%20content%20at%20China's%20request%20in%20other%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20appeals%20court%20wrote%20that%20TikTok%20%26quot%3Bnever%20squarely%20denies%26quot%3B%20that%20it%20has%20ever%20manipulated%20content%20on%20its%20platform%20at%20China's%20request%2C%20which%20it%20says%20is%20%26quot%3Bstriking%26quot%3B%20given%20the%20intelligence%20community's%20concerns.%20The%20court%20concluded%20that%20Bytedance%20and%20TikTok%20have%20%26quot%3Ba%20demonstrated%20history%26quot%3B%20of%20manipulating%20content%20in%20other%20countries%2C%20sometimes%20at%20the%20request%20of%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20conclusion%20rests%20on%20more%20than%20mere%20speculation%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judges%20wrote%20in%20the%20court%20opinion.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20the%20Government's%20'informed%20judgment'%20to%20which%20we%20give%20great%20weight%20in%20this%20context%2C%20even%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20'concrete%20evidence'%20on%20the%20likelihood%20of%20PRC-directed%20censorship%20of%20TikTok%20in%20the%20United%20States.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20argued%20in%20court%20that%20its%20%26quot%3Brecommendation%20engine%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20algorithm%2C%20is%20not%20based%20in%20China%20because%20it%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foracle-cloud-business-tiktok-biden-china-rule-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estored%20in%20the%20Oracle%20cloud%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20court%20said%20that%20while%20this%20is%20correct%2C%20ByteDance%20still%20controls%20the%20source%20code%20for%20TikTok%2C%20including%20the%20recommendation%20engine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTikTok%20is%20therefore%20correct%20to%20say%20the%20recommendation%20engine%20'is%20stored%20in%20the%20Oracle%20cloud%2C'%20but%20gains%20nothing%20by%20flyspecking%20the%20Government's%20characterization%20of%20the%20recommendation%20engine%20still%20being%20in%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20document%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20TikTok%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20TikTok%20ban%20%26quot%3Bwas%20conceived%20and%20pushed%20through%20based%20on%20inaccurate%2C%20flawed%2C%20and%20hypothetical%20information%2C%20resulting%20in%20outright%20censorship%20of%20the%20American%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20an%20established%20historical%20record%20of%20protecting%20Americans'%20right%20to%20free%20speech%2C%20and%20we%20expect%20they%20will%20do%20just%20that%20on%20this%20important%20constitutional%20issue%2C%26quot%3B%20TikTok%20said%20in%20the%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20many%20social%20media%20networks%2C%20TikTok%20has%20faced%20intense%20scrutiny%20for%20how%20the%20app%20is%20used%20to%20influence%20elections.%20The%20company%20this%20week%20announced%20that%20it%20removed%20three%20%26quot%3Binfluence%20networks%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20app%20that%20attempted%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-election-interference-romania-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimpact%20an%20election%20in%20Romania%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20a%20probe%20by%20the%20country's%20defense%20council.%20The%20company%20said%20it%20removed%20at%20least%2040%20similar%20influence%20campaigns%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-china-propaganda-content-court-ruling-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733605871000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6754ab848fbb2783ed306f74%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-china-propaganda-content-court-ruling-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20its%20ruling%20on%20the%20TikTok%20ban%2C%20a%20court%20said%20that%20while%20the%20US%20provided%20no%20evidence%20China%20manipulates%20content%20in%20the%20country%2C%20it's%20still%20possible.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kniemeyer%40insider.com%20(Kenneth%20Niemeyer)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A23%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-china-propaganda-content-court-ruling-2024-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22With%20%E2%80%98Carnival%2C%E2%80%99%20Ye%20and%20Ty%20Dolla%20%24ign%20Shouted%20Down%20Controversy%20With%20a%20Viral%20X-Rated%20Hook%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%